\SE[11]It went perfectly! \SE[48]...or so I'd like to
say. \SE[48]I couldn't find the actual item. This is the
only thing that caught my eye.

\SE[4]Is this... a key? \SE[3]It's quite big... It doesn't
seem like something you would use for a door. \SE[2]I wonder
where this is used...?

\SE[1]Don't you know either, sis? \SE[3]Then, could it be
something newly created...? \SE[1]Do you have any idea,
Nikita- san?

\SE[52]A key...? \SE[4]It's not something we usually
use.... \SE[52]I'm sorry... I don't really know....

\SE[2]Hmm... I have some clues, but I'm at a dead end...
\SE[3]I wonder what to do.

\SE[2]If neither Cat nor I know... \!\SE[3]And even Nikita
doesn't know...

\SE[50]It's not something new that Nikita knows...
\!\SE[51]And it's not something old that we know...
\!\SE[74]If it's neither of those...

\SE[4]Something even older... I wonder. \SE[3]Perhaps it's
something from before the mansion was built...

\SE[2]When it comes to something from that era, someone who
already knows... \.\SE[4]Ah.

\SE[4]Let's go ask the gardener, Yard. \!\SE[3]They might
know something.

\SE[2]Nikita, come with us. Depending on the situation, we
might escape together. \SE[3]Don't worry. I will guarantee
your safety.

\SE[45] (I wonder... these two... \SE[13] They seem to
have become close without me noticing... \SE[45] I can smell
it... Yes, I can definitely smell it...)
